LongDescription: Lineships form the primary fighting element of the Protectorate fleet.  Rapidly refit from seized commercial freighters and pressed into service during the blockade of the Kribensis gate.  This series of lineship is built from container carriers, designed to carry hundreds of boxes of cargo in racks along the outside of the hull.  These ships primarily serve as missile and utility carriers.
FlavorText:
Vance,

Excellent work in Kribensis, your efforts have given us the means to establish a proper foothold without needing to go through Bethel and her Barons. I'd prefer it if we didn't have to use QEDs to do that but the anchor point should serve just fine, I'll make sure you're properly rewarded for your initiative and thinking.

Additionally, I'm grateful for your container ships, they will be invaluable. While I can't convince Command Engineering or the Otdel to 'load it with enough guns to level Shelter', I have heard rumblings about converting the spare stock of containers into effective weapons that should function perfect for the ambushing role I have in mind for them. I've asked Amelie to determine the combat capability of fixed guns on these hulls but it's becoming apparent that our bulkers will be better suited for that.

- Constantine
